<br>
While <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Caster versus Melee Balance</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is important, and is probably out of whack, it is difficult to discuss as these archetypes represent two opposite ends of the spectrum and each ones strengths are very different from the other and difficult to compare.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Casters</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Priests</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are more similar.  Both are defined largely by spells, and trade damage for utility and spells for melee ability.<br>
<br>
It is easy to compare damage output of classes, and this can and has be done <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> ad nauseum</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  What I seek to compare here is the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> non-damage utility</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, so we can see if the archetypes are balanced, and if not, how they can be.<br>
<br>
If I can ask nicely to minimize the comparison of damage dealing spells for a while, I would appreciate it.  Those kind of comparisons are relatively easily done, and are ultimately meaningless when isolated from the context of utility.<br>
<br>
This is not to disparage anyone's contribution here, but simply to try to focus the discussion.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
ArchAbuser of EZCodes<br>
