I would just like to say that you've some seriously unfounded hate for druids.  They might seem good when you just list what then can possibly do.  However, more often then not, in a standard xp group they don't do a whole lot.  <br>
In your standard group a druid will usually be doing the following:<br>
<br>
- Snare. Usually the only reason to get a druid.  Rangers, necros, wizards, SKs, bards, and some troll shaman can do this too.  As well as bring much more to a group.<br>
- Back up heal.  Sounds good but is usually not needed.  A cleric can keep a group healed quite well by them selves in most circumstances.<br>
- Buff.  If you have a cleric you can forget this one.<br>
- DS.  Advantages and disadvantages are the same for the magician ds.<br>
- Regen.  Useful for shaman and necros.  Not as useful for anyone else.  The difference it makes is fairly unimpressive.  Only a decent ability if you're doing it for free via velious quest bp.<br>
- Damage.  You can't nuke more than once or twice per mob and keep up with pulls in a group usually.  That's about 1200 damage.  Mages do more than that without using pets.<br>
- Debuff.  Ro's Firey Agroing.  If you notice the difference it makes you'll be the only one that does.<br>
<br>
All in all a druid isn't bringing that much to a group.  They might have a lot of utility, but they contribute little.<br>
