I'm of the opinion druids do need some work.  I have been able to do some fun stuff with druids as cc or only healer, but they could use a boost in the healing area.  I really dislike being reliant on clerics so much.  Sure you don't need them in xp groups much anymore...well at all anymore, but since we like talking about raiding, being dependant on clerics as the only healer blows.  Sure druids and shamans should never get ch, but something more viable needs to be brought in.  <br>
<br>
Seems alot of you have a ton of druids on your servers.  Well, mine has a ton too.  Yep, every other melee char has a druid port whore.  Still quite a few druid mains wandering out there, but for some reason most of them seem to stick to endless kiting, I haven't figured out why yet.  Of the ones who actually decide to raid, they will almost exclusively wind up healing.  Their nuking opurtunities are as non-existant as clerics.  Their nukes fall victim to the exact same problem mage ones do.  They have something better to do with their mana alot of the time.  They heal, we give mana to people who can heal.  They become as important as a 20/20 weapon in the hands of a purecaster, badass when first seen, but when reality hits you you see it doesn't really matter much.<br>
<br>
Like the druids said, they need better heals.  The better heals they get, the less they will use their nukes.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Xp zones are sooooooooo gimped already that there is really *no* point in trying to keep caster upgrades in line with them, doing that will only keep us at our current strength.  I dunno about you, but when I walk into seb and see a paladin and shaman holding jail, monk holding exit, mage and chanter holding disco, and a lone *real* group doing nec/guard the reasoning behind keeping our power balanced in zones like that flew out the window.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usepisis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sepisis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#333333>(4/8/02 5:06:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=178.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: TABOO TOPIC: Caster versus Priest Balance</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Druids have a superior DD spell listing and so how is it possible for a mage to out damage a druid without a pet??????<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
